
abstract=The Cultural Artefact Contextual Ontology (CACAO) provides a semantic framework for modeling and contextualizing cultural heritage artifacts, integrating concepts from CIDOC-CRM, PROV-O, and other established ontologies to support comprehensive documentation of cultural objects, their provenance, and associated metadata.
