description=The Cultural Artefact Contextual Ontology (CACAO) is a formal ontology developed to support the semantic description and contextualization of cultural heritage artifacts. CACAO integrates multiple well-established ontologies including CIDOC-CRM 7.1.3 for cultural heritage documentation, PROV-O for provenance tracking, FOAF for agent representation, Schema.org for web interoperability, and ODRL for rights management. The ontology provides approximately 80 core CACAO classes covering various aspects of cultural artifact documentation, complemented by extensive property definitions and mappings to external vocabularies. CACAO is designed to facilitate interoperability across cultural heritage information systems and support comprehensive documentation of cultural objects, their history, provenance, and associated rights and permissions.
introduction=CACAO is part of the REEVALUATE project and follows OBO Foundry best practices for ontology development. The ontology is actively maintained and developed using the Ontology Development Kit (ODK).
